; mongod lifecycle (native): detect the system mongod, launch a managed dev/test instance with its
; own data dir + port, wait until it accepts connections, and stop it gracefully (SIGTERM then
; SIGKILL, ephemeral data dir auto-removed). Pure process management (Unix) — no driver, no jsoo.
; The CLI's dev/test orchestration uses this; the libmongoc driver talks to the launched instance.
(library
 (name fennec_mongo_mongod)
 (public_name fennec-mongo.mongod)
 (libraries unix))
